name: Chinampa
description: This artwork cultivates Mexican data for the internet 3.0 collective memory. The word chinampa, comes from the Nahuatl chinampan, which means "in the fence of reeds", it is an artificial cultivation system, built in areas where water is the main natural resource present in the environment. They are built in order to grow plants, vegetables and vegetables for self-consumption and local markets. By 1519, this method of cultivation occupied almost the entire Xochimilco lake in Mexico.
